Package simulator.elevatorcontrol

Contains classes that manipulate the simulated environmental objects.

See:
          Description

Class Summary
DesiredFloorCanPayloadTranslator This is an example CAN payload translator for desired floor messages.
DriveCommandCanPayloadTranslator Can payload translator for the drive command, which includes a speed value and a direction.
DriveControl There is one DriveControl, which controls the elevator Drive (the main motor moving Car Up and Down).
MessageDictionary This class defines constants for CAN IDs that are used throughout the simulator.
SampleDispatcherMonitor This example monitor shows how to use the RuntimeMonitor hooks to check for fast speed between floors.
SamplePerformanceMonitor This monitoring class gives you a starting point for the performance checks you will do in project 7.
Utility This class provides some example utility classes that might be useful in more than one spot.
